      <tr id="andor" data-drop="<ol> <li>My father Mikhail says that Andor has not been home since yesterday. I should go look for him in the village. </li> <li>Leonid tells me that he saw Andor talking to Gruil. I should go ask Gruil if he knows more. </li> <li>Gruil wants me to bring him a poison gland. Then he might talk more. He tells me that some poisonous snakes have such a gland. </li> <li>Gruil tells me that Andor was looking for someone called Umar. I should go ask his friend Gaela in Fallhaven to the east. </li> <li>I talked to Gaela in Fallhaven. He tells me to go see Bucus and ask about the Thieves' Guild. </li> <li>Bucus has allowed me to enter the hatch in the derelict house in Fallhaven. I should go talk to Umar. </li> <li>Umar in the Fallhaven Thieves' Guild recognized me, but must have me mixed up with Andor. Apparently, Andor has been to see him. </li> <li>Umar told me that Andor went to see a potion maker called Lodar. I should search for his hideaway. </li> <li>I heard a story in Loneford, where it seemed like Andor had been in Loneford, and that he might have had something to do with the illness that the people are suffering from there. I am not sure if it actually was Andor. If it was Andor, why would he have made the people of Loneford ill? </li> <li>I have found the potion-maker Lodar, and heard his story about Andor. Andor went to visit Lodar in his hideaway to get a sample of something called Narwood extract. Lodar happened to notice that there was someone travelling together with Andor, that hid among the trees and did not seem to want Lodar to spot him. </li> <li>Shortly after Andor and the person he was travelling with had left, strange things started to happen in the woods around Lodar's hideaway, and Lodar himself seemed to be affected by it somehow. Lodar believes that something disturbed the tomb below his cabin, and awoke the Hira'zinn. </li> <li>Since I helped Lodar defeat the Hira'zinn, he promised to help me in return. He gave me a piece of paper that should allow me to enter the Valanyr temple of the Shadow in Nor City. He told me to seek out lady Lydalon in the temple for further assistance. </li> <li>All clues so far as to where Andor went point to Nor City. I should travel to Nor City by following the Duleian road to the southeast and look for more clues there. </li> </ol> <table> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/monsterlist.php#buceth%22 class=%22at-icon size1x1 unique%22><img src=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/drawable/0.7.0/monsters_men2.png%22 alt=%22monsters_men2.png%22 style=%22margin: -0px 0px 0px -224px%22></a></td> <td class=%22left%22>Buceth</td><td></td> </tr> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/npclist.php#bucus%22 class=%22at-icon size1x1%22><img src=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/drawable/0.7.0/monsters_rogue1.png%22 alt=%22monsters_rogue1.png%22 style=%22margin: -0px 0px 0px -0px%22></a></td> <td class=%22left%22>Bucus</td><td></td> </tr> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/npclist.php#gaela%22 class=%22at-icon size1x1%22><img src=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/drawable/0.7.0/monsters_men2.png%22 alt=%22monsters_men2.png%22 style=%22margin: -0px 0px 0px -288px%22></a></td> <td class=%22left%22>Gaela</td><td></td> </tr> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/npclist.php#gruil%22 class=%22at-icon size1x1%22><img src=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/drawable/0.7.0/monsters_rogue1.png%22 alt=%22monsters_rogue1.png%22 style=%22margin: -0px 0px 0px -0px%22></a></td> <td class=%22left%22>Gruil</td><td></td> </tr> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/npclist.php#leonid%22 class=%22at-icon size1x1%22><img src=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/drawable/0.7.0/monsters_men.png%22 alt=%22monsters_men.png%22 style=%22margin: -0px 0px 0px -96px%22></a></td> <td class=%22left%22>Leonid</td><td></td> </tr> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/npclist.php#lodar%22 clas