      <tr id="bwm_agent" data-drop="<ol> <li>I met a man seeking help for his settlement, the 'Blackwater Mountain'. Supposedly, his settlement is being attacked by monsters and bandits, and they need help from the outside. </li> <li>I have agreed to help the man and Blackwater Mountain in dealing with the problem. </li> <li>The man told me to meet him on the other side of the collapsed mine. He will crawl through the mine shaft and I will descend into the pitch-black abandoned mine. </li> <li>I have navigated through the pitch-black abandoned mine, and met the man on the other side. He seemed very anxious about telling me to head straight to the east once I exit the mine. I should meet the man at the bottom of the mountain to the east. </li> <li>I heard a story about Prim and the Blackwater Mountain settlement fighting against each other. </li> <li>I should follow the mountain path up the mountain to the Blackwater settlement. </li> <li>I met the man again on my way up to Blackwater Mountain. I should proceed further up the mountain. </li> <li>I have made it up to the snow-filled parts of the Blackwater Mountain. The man told me to proceed further up the mountain. Apparently, the Blackwater Mountain settlement is close by. </li> <li>I have reached the Blackwater mountain settlement. I should find and talk to their battle master, Harlenn. </li> <li>I have spoken to Harlenn in the Blackwater Mountain settlement. Apparently, the settlement is under attack by a number of monsters, the Aulaeth and white wyrms. On top of that, they are being attacked by the people of Prim. </li> <li>Harlenn thinks the people of Prim are behind the monster attacks somehow. </li> <li>Harlenn wants me to give a message to Guthbered of Prim. Either the people of Prim stop their attacks on the Blackwater Mountain settlement, or they will have to be dealt with themselves. I should go talk to Guthbered in Prim. </li> <li>Guthbered denies that the people of Prim have anything to do with the monster attacks on the Blackwater mountain settlement. I should go talk to Harlenn </li> <li>Harlenn is sure that the people of Prim are behind the attacks somehow. </li> <li>Harlenn wants me to go to Prim and look for signs that they are preparing for an attack on the settlement. I should go look for clues around where Guthbered stays. </li> <li>I have found some plans in Prim about recruiting mercenaries and attacking the Blackwater Mountain settlement. I should go talk to Harlenn immediately. </li> <li class=%22exp%22>Harlenn thanked me for investigating the attack plans.<b>(1150 XP)</b> </li> <li>To make the attacks on the Blackwater Mountain settlement stop, Harlenn wants me to assassinate Guthbered in Prim. </li> <li>I have started a fight with Guthbered. </li> <li class=%22exp%22>I told Guthbered that I was sent to kill him, but I let him live. He thanked me deeply, and left Prim.<b>(2100 XP)</b> </li> <li>I have told Harlenn that Guthbered is gone. </li> <li class=%22exp%22>Harlenn thanked me for the help I have provided. Hopefully, the attacks on the Blackwater Mountain settlement should stop now.<b>(5000 XP)</b> </li> <li class=%22end%22>I am now trusted in the Blackwater Mountain settlement, and all services should be available for me to use. <b>[End of quest]</b></li> <li class=%22end%22>I have decided to not help the people of the Blackwater Mountain settlement. <b>[End of quest]</b></li> <li class=%22end%22>Since I am helping Prim, Harlenn no longer wants to talk to me. <b>[End of quest]</b></li> </ol> <table> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/npclist.php#agent1%22 class=%22at-icon size1x1 unique%22><img src=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/drawable/0.7.0/monsters_men.png%22 alt=%22monsters_men.png%22 style=%22margin: -0px 0px 0px -128px%22></a></td> <td class=%22left%22>Agent</td><td></td> </tr> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/npclist.php#agent2%22 class=%22at-icon size1x1 unique%22><img src=%22http://andorstr