      <tr id="charwood1" data-drop="<ol> <li>I heard a rumor that some mining town in the Charwood forest, northwest of the Foaming Flask tavern, have had some troubles recently. I should try to find the Charwood cabin and find out what has happened. </li> <li>I heard someone mentioning that the mining town of Charwood heights have had some troubles recently. I should search for the Charwood cabin in the forest northwest of the Foaming Flask tavern. </li> <li>I have found the Charwood cabin in the forest northwest of the Foaming Flask tavern. </li> <li>Maevalia in the Charwood cabin told me a story about how their mining settlement was attacked by some monsters, forcing them to flee down the mountain. They are still missing several of their friends and relatives from the Charwood heights, either killed or captured by the monsters. </li> <li>In particular, Maevalia mentions four people that are greatly missed; their former leader Morenavia, their weapons trainer Falothen, the healer Ayell and their armorer Fayvara. </li> <li>I have agreed to help the people of Charwood find their missing people. </li> <li>The guard outside the Charwood cabin allowed me to enter the hills ahead. I should keep to the east and then head north. </li> <li>I encountered one of the monsters that Maevalia spoke of. The monster spoke of someone or something called 'The Thukuzun'. </li> <li>I have found Falothen, the weapons trainer of the Charwood heights, and freed him of the restraints that held him. He will try to make his way back to the Charwood cabin himself. </li> <li>I have found some skeletal remains, containing a ring with the insignia 'Morenavia'. This must be the former leader of the Charwood hills. </li> <li>I have found the armorer Fayvara, and freed her of the restraints that held her. She will try to make her way back to the Charwood cabin herself. </li> <li>I have found some skeletal remains, containing a ring with the insignia 'Ayell'. This must be the remains of the Charwoo