      <tr id="lodar" data-drop="<ol> <li>I should find a potion maker called Lodar. Umar in the Fallhaven Thieves' Guild told me that I will need to know the right words to pass a guardian in order to reach Lodar's hideaway. </li> <li>Umar told me I should go see someone called Ogam in Vilegard. Ogam can supply me with the right words to reach Lodar's hideaway. </li> <li>I have visited Ogam in southwest Vilegard. He was talking in what seemed like riddles. I could barely make out some details when I asked about Lodar's hideaway. 'Halfway between the Shadow and the light. Rocky formations.' and the words 'Glow of the Shadow.' were among the things he said. I am not sure what they mean. </li> <li>I have found a formation of rocks on the Duleian Road. It does not look like they were naturally placed, but rather that they are meant to symbolize something. </li> <li class=%22exp%22>Could this be the 'rocky formation' that the old man Ogam mentioned? If that is the case, then this might be a clue as to where Andor went.<b>(1500 XP)</b> </li> <li>In the woods close to the rocky formation, I encountered a creature blocking the way into the forest. </li> <li class=%22exp%22>By speaking the words that Ogam had mentioned, the creature moved out of the way, and almost seemed to welcome me further into the forest.<b>(3000 XP)</b> </li> <li>I encountered a guard from Feygard in the woods. He told me a tale of a madman that the guards from Feygard are searching for. The madman is wanted for a number of reasons that he would not disclose. He warned me both about the twisty mazes ahead, and about the madman. Apparently, several guards have gone missing after venturing forth, either by getting lost in the maze, or by something that the madman has done to them. </li> <li>Before leaving, the guard warned me both about the twisty mazes ahead, and about the madman. Apparently, several guards have gone missing after venturing forth, either by getting lost in the maze, or by something that the madman has done to them. </li> <li class=%22exp%22>I found another rocky formation that looked out of place.<b>(2000 XP)</b> </li> <li>I encountered another guard from Feygard, disoriented and lost. The things he said did not make sense. </li> <li>I encountered another guard from Feygard, that seemed to be affected by something. He attacked me without provocation. </li> <li>I encountered another guard from Feygard, that rambled of something that 'lurks underneath'. He attacked me without provocation. </li> <li class=%22exp%22>I found yet another rocky formation that looked out of place.<b>(2000 XP)</b> </li> <li class=%22exp%22>In a well-hidden cave, I encountered yet another rocky formation that looked similar to the other ones that I've already seen. I must be getting close to whatever these formations lead to.<b>(2000 XP)</b> </li> <li>In the cave, I reached what looks like a tomb. I was unable to venture further into the tomb because of something that held me back. </li> <li class=%22end exp%22>After navigating through the immense twisty green maze and the damp cave, I have reached a cabin in a clearing. The cabin is occupied by the potion-maker called Lodar.<b>(5000 XP)</b> <b>[End of quest]</b></li> </ol> <table> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/npclist.php#lodar%22 class=%22at-icon size1x1%22><img src=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/drawable/0.7.0/monsters_rltiles1.png%22 alt=%22monsters_rltiles1.png%22 style=%22margin: -96px 0px 0px -544px%22></a></td> <td class=%22left%22>Lodar</td><td></td> </tr> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/npclist.php#lodar0_g%22 class=%22at-icon size1x1 unique%22><img src=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/drawable/0.7.0/monsters_tometik5.png%22 alt=%22monsters_tometik5.png%22 style=%22margin: -416px 0px 0px -64px%22></a></td> <td class=%22left%22>Forest guardian</td><td></td> </tr> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/npclist.php#lodar_fg1%22 class=%22at-icon size