      <tr id="lodar13_rest" data-drop="<ol> <li>In the maze of green vines east of the Duleian road, I met a guard named Aulowenn from Feygard, guarding some crates. She told me that she was part of a larger group of guards searching for a madman that supposedly hides somewhere in the nearby hills, but that the other guards are now dead or missing. </li> <li>Aulowenn requested my help in defeating a monster that haunts the grave of her fellow guards to the east. She warned me that the foul beast will most likely try to trick me into listening to its story. </li> <li>I have met the creature that Aulowenn spoke of. </li> <li>I listened to the creature's story. Its name is Tiqui, and he is the head of his clan. Apparently, the guards have been ruthlessly killing off his kin. He asked me to kill the guard for him, as revenge for what they have done. </li> <li>The creature tried to trick me into listening to its story. </li> <li>I attacked the creature before it could spew out more of its foul lies. </li> <li>I attacked Aulowenn. </li> <li>Aulowenn thanked me for bringing peace to the grave of her fallen companions by killing the creature. </li> <li>Tiqui was overjoyed that I helped him kill the guard for him. He promised that if we ever run into each other again, he'd help me somehow. </li> <li class=%22end exp%22>I am now able to use Aulowenn's bed whenever I wish to rest.<b>(3000 XP)</b> <b>[End of quest]</b></li> <li class=%22end%22>I will not be able to resolve the conflict between Aulowenn and her attacker. <b>[End of quest]</b></li> </ol> <table> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/monsterlist.php#aulowenn%22 class=%22at-icon size1x1 unique%22><img src=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/drawable/0.7.0/monsters_rltiles1.png%22 alt=%22monsters_rltiles1.png%22 style=%22margin: -128px 0px 0px -192px%22></a></td> <td class=%22left%22>Aulowenn</td><td></td> </tr> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/monsterlist.php#tiqui%22 class=%22