      <tr id="remgard" data-drop="<ol> <li>I have reached the bridge to enter the town of Remgard. According to the bridge guard, the town is closed for outsiders to enter, and no-one is currently allowed to leave. They are investigating some disappearances of some of the townspeople. </li> <li>I have offered my assistance in helping the people of Remgard investigate what has happened to the townspeople that have disappeared. </li> <li>The bridge guard has asked me to investigate an abandoned house to the east along the northern shore of the lake. I should be wary of any inhabitants that may be there. </li> <li class=%22exp%22>I have reported back to the bridge guard that I met Algangror in the abandoned house.<b>(3000 XP)</b> </li> <li class=%22exp%22>I have reported back to the bridge guard that the abandoned house was empty.<b>(3000 XP)</b> </li> <li>I have been granted entrance into Remgard. I should go visit Jhaeld, the town elder, to talk about what the next step should be. Jhaeld can probably be found in the tavern to the southeast. </li> <li>Jhaeld was rather arrogant, but told me that they have had a problem with people disappearing for a while now. They have no clue what could be causing it. </li> <li>I should visit four people in Remgard, and ask them about any clues on what might have happened to the missing people. </li> <li>First is Norath, whose wife Bethir has disappeared. Norath can be found in the south-westernmost farmhouse. </li> <li>Second, I should go talk to the Knights of Elythom, here in the tavern. </li> <li>Third, I should go talk to the old woman Duaina in her house to the south. </li> <li>Lastly, I should talk to Rothses, the armorer. He lives on the west side of town. </li> <li>I tried to tell Jhaeld about Algangror, but he dismissed me as he had not heard me. </li> <li>I have talked to Norath. He and his wife had been fighting recently, but he has no idea on what may have happened to her. </li> <li>The Knights of Elythom in the Remgard tavern have had one of their knights disappearing recently. No one noticed anything when she disappeared, however. </li> <li>Duaina has seen me in her visions. I did not understand all that she spoke of, but the parts that were clear were that me and Andor were parts of a larger plot. I wonder what this means? She did not speak of any disappearing people however, not that I could understand anyway. </li> <li>Rothses told me that Bethir visited him the night before she disappeared, to sell some equipment. He did not see where she went after that. </li> <li>I have talked to all of the people that Jhaeld wanted me to talk to, but did not get any information from any of them about what may have happened to the missing people. I should go back to Jhaeld and ask what his plans are next. </li> <li class=%22exp%22>Jhaeld was really upset that I did not find out anything from the people that I was sent to talk to.<b>(15000 XP)</b> </li> <li class=%22end%22>If I still want to help Jhaeld and the people of Remgard, I should look for clues in other places. <b>[End of quest]</b></li> <li class=%22end%22>Jhaeld does not want to talk to me. I will not help them find out what happened to the missing people of Remgard. <b>[End of quest]</b></li> </ol> <table> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/npclist.php#duaina%22 class=%22at-icon size1x1%22><img src=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/drawable/0.7.0/monsters_ld1.png%22 alt=%22monsters_ld1.png%22 style=%22margin: -224px 0px 0px -448px%22></a></td> <td class=%22left%22>Duaina</td><td></td> </tr> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/npclist.php#jhaeld%22 class=%22at-icon size1x1%22><img src=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/drawable/0.7.0/monsters_mage.png%22 alt=%22monsters_mage.png%22 style=%22margin: -0px 0px 0px -0px%22></a></td> <td class=%22left%22>Jhaeld</td><td></td> </tr> <tr> <td><a href=%22http://andorstrail.irkalla.cz/0.7.0/npclist.php#krell%22 class=%22at-icon size1x1%22><img src=%22h